    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>128600</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>ων<choice> <unclear>μ</unclear><unclear>ν</unclear></choice></orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2"/><w lemma="δεκάτα"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">δεκάτα</supplied>ν</w> <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι">ἀν<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">έθηκε</supplied></w>
                    <lb n="2a"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraduisible (voir commentaire).</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Not usefully translatable (see commentary).</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraducibile (vedi commento).</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>غير قابل للترجمة بشكل جيد (راجع التعليق على النقش).</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>The third letter preserved at line 1 does not seem to be an iota. So the dative of the Apollo's name should be excluded. This first line in larger 
               characters might have the dedicant's name, maybe a name ending with <foreign xml:lang="grc">-ων</foreign> and the first letter of his father's name.</p>
	           <p>Although very fragmentary, the second line might have the usual formula of dedication of the tithe. The whole is very hypothetical.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
